      "digital_id",
      "biometric_collection"
    ],
    "jurisdiction": "National",
    "description": "Establishes voluntary accreditation scheme for digital identity service providers. Creates Trust Framework Authority and Trust Framework Board to oversee standards for privacy, security, and data sharing. While currently voluntary, establishes infrastructure for potential future mandatory digital ID requirements.",
    "sources": [
      {
        "url": "https://www.legislation.govt.nz/act/public/2023/0013/latest/whole.html",
        "type": "primary",
        "description": "NZ Government - Digital Identity Services Trust Framework Act 2023 full text"
      },
      {
        "url": "https://www.minterellison.co.nz/insights/government-releases-digital-identity-services-trust-framework-rules",
        "type": "news",
        "description": "Legal analysis of Trust Framework Rules release (Nov 2024)"
      },
      {
        "url": "https://privacymatters.dlapiper.com/2023/03/new-zealand-digital-identity-services-trust-framework-bill-passes-final-reading/",
        "type": "news",
        "description": "DLA Piper analysis of Act passage and implications"
      }
    ],
    "notes": "Came into effect 1 July 2024. Trust Framework Rules released November 2024. Accreditation is voluntary but creates pathway to future mandatory requirements. Includes Māori Advisory Group for te ao Māori perspectives on identity. Rules cover consent, privacy impact assessments, security, and data management. Critics note it does little to address bigger issues of digital rights and online identity data."
  },
  
  {
    "id": "NZ-2025-BIOMETRIC",
    "commonName": "Biometric Processing Privacy Code",
