      },
      {
        "url": "https://www.simpsongrierson.com/insights-news/legal-updates/new-privacy-rules-for-biometrics-in-new-zealand",
        "type": "news",
        "description": "Simpson Grierson legal analysis of Code requirements"
      }
    ],
    "notes": "Came into force 3 November 2025. Grace period until 3 August 2026 for existing biometric systems. NZ Council for Civil Liberties strongly criticized for not going far enough, calling for ban on Remote Biometric Identification (RBI). Code recognizes 'chilling effect' on protests and rights to assembly. Māori stakeholders raised concerns about bias and discrimination. Consumer NZ criticized removal of 'informed consent and ability to opt out' safeguard from draft. Foodstuffs North Island facial recognition trial in supermarkets cited as concerning example."
  },
  
  {
