    },
    "categories": [
      "biometric_collection",
      "worker_surveillance"
    ],
    "jurisdiction": "National",
    "description": "Legalized experimental AI-powered video surveillance for 2024 Paris Olympics, including algorithmic crowd analysis and biometric detection of 'suspicious behavior.' Law was temporary but established precedent and infrastructure for permanent deployment. Expanded police powers to use drones and facial recognition.",
    "sources": [
      {
        "url": "https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/jorf/id/JORFTEXT000047571222",
        "type": "primary",
        "description": "Legifrance - Loi JO2024 official text"
      },
      {
        "url": "https://www.laquadrature.net/",
        "type": "civil_society",
        "description": "La Quadrature du Net - French digital rights organization (ongoing surveillance criticism)"
      }
    ],
    "notes": "Temporary law for Olympic period but established permanent surveillance infrastructure. AI video analysis including crowd density detection, abandoned object detection, and behavior analysis. CNIL raised concerns about proportionality. La Quadrature du Net challenged facial recognition use before CNIL. Law expanded to allow police drone surveillance. Post-Olympics, infrastructure remains and has been used for other events. Sets dangerous precedent for 'temporary' surveillance becoming permanent."
  },

