      }
    ],
    "notes": "ECtHR Grand Chamber judgment May 25, 2021 found Swedish signals intelligence regime violated Article 8 ECHR due to ineffective oversight. 2024 amendments failed to address core issue: Foreign Intelligence Inspectorate cannot render legally binding decisions that unlawful surveillance must cease. Inspectorate can only act if FRA acts 'outside bounds of permit' - but permits set broad framework allowing compliance while breaching Convention. Centrum för rättvisa (Centre for Justice) continues litigation. SOU 2024:59 proposed further expansion including wartime domestic surveillance. FRA operates under Ministry of Defence. 16 years of bulk interception without effective oversight."
  },
  
